      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PINITO (1) settled a long way back and couldn't get involved last start over 1600m at this track. Looked a bit flat that day so an extra 500m might be what she needs. Three-time stakes winner who has the class to take care of this line-up. HYPERBOLIC (3) found the line well to get up for third in the same race as PINITO here a fortnight ago. Genuine mare who is going better than most of these, although she is yet to be tried beyond the mile. WALSH BAY (2) travelled back in the field and made no impression in the 2400m Premier's Cup last time out. Handy mare who will appreciate this drop in grade. Can find form without surprising. GEEMES (6) made steady ground without threatening when fresh from a spell over the Randwick mile recently. Has a fine second-up record so she can improve enough to play a significant role. SUN WORSHIPPER (4) was very good in the Ipswich Cup last weekend and is a chance if that run has not flattened her.",
